ciscoSlbExtMIB.description: The extended MIB for managing Server Load Balancing Manager(s). This MIB extends the SLB management functionality in the CISCO-SLB-MIB. The Cisco Content Switching Module (CSM) product is the first SLB product to support this MIB. SLB: Server Load Balancing. Server load balancing provides for the balancing of packets and connections arriving at the SLB device across a number of other devices, such as real servers, firewalls, or caches. A system containing an SLB device typically exhibits higher performance, scalability, and reliability than any of the devices being load balanced. An SLB device determines how to handle incoming frames and connections according to the contents of incoming data and various configuration options. In determining how to handle incoming data, an SLB device may examine the data at any OSI layer, including Layer 7. This MIB includes instrumentation for the manager-side implementation of the Dynamic Feedback Protocol (DFP). A DFP manager uses the DFP protocol to communicate with DFP agents in order to obtain information about the current load and available capacity of devices. Acronyms and terms: SLB Server Load Balancing VIP Virtual Server IP address NAT Network Address Translation SF Serverfarm FT Fault Tolerance SSL Secure Sockets Layer TLS Transport Layer Security

SlbObjectNameString.name: SlbObjectNameString
SlbObjectNameString.description: The name of an associated SLB object. All SLB object names are in uppercase.

SlbFunctionNameString.name: SlbFunctionNameString
SlbFunctionNameString.description: The label name for a section of the executable script. A section of script is a logical container which includes the executable instructions to perform a certain task. The Tool Command Language (Tcl) is one of the well-defined scripting languages. The language is depending on individual implementation of an SLB device. The scripts will be imported into an SLB system as parts of the user's configurations. The purpose of supporting scripting language is to extend the existing functionalities in a particular SLB implementation. The SlbFunctionNameString must only contain these characters: - lowercase character 'a' to 'z'. - uppercase character 'A' to 'Z'. - numeric character '0' to '9'. - the underscore '_' character.

SlbUrlString.name: SlbUrlString
SlbUrlString.description: The octet string containing the Uniform Resource Locator (URL) information. It is in human-readable form.

SlbRegularExpression.name: SlbRegularExpression
SlbRegularExpression.description: A regular expression of length 0 to 255. Regular expressions are typically used for matching fields in Layer 7 data streams, such as URLs or Cookies in HTTP. The following syntax is based on the file name matching algorithm commonly employed in UNIX : '*' matches zero or more characters; '?' matches exactly one character; '\' means escaped character, e.g., '\*' matches the character '*'; a bracketed range matches any single character from the range, e.g. [0-9] matches '0', '2', and '9', but not 'a'; a leading ^ in a range means don't match any in the range; '+' matches any sequence of one or more characters; '.' matches any single character; All other characters represent themselves. '\a' matches alert (ASCII 7); '\b' matches backspace (ASCII 8); '\f' matches form-feed (ASCII 12); '\n' matches newline (ASCII 10); '\r' matches carriage return (ASCII 13); '\t' matches tab (ASCII 9); '\v' matches vertical tab (ASCII 11); '\0' matches null (ASCII 0); '\\' matches backslash; '\x##' matches the ASCII character whose hexadecimal representation is ##.

SlbFailAction.name: SlbFailAction
SlbFailAction.description: The current action setting for a server farm when a real server has failed. 'noAction' : No additional action besides taking the server out of service. 'purgeConns' : Purge all connections to this real server. 'reassignConns' : Re-assign all connections to another real server. 'undefined' : New action not yet defined.

SlbIpAdvertise.name: SlbIpAdvertise
SlbIpAdvertise.description: The current advertise option for the virtual server IP address. 'alwaysAdvertise' : Advertise VIP if configured. 'activeAdvertise' : Advertise VIP only if virtual server is active. 'undefined' : New type not yet defined.

SlbStickyType.name: SlbStickyType
SlbStickyType.description: The current type of the Sticky Group. A Sticky Group is a list of rules mapping incoming connection parameters, such as source IP address, to specific real servers. If an incoming connection matches a rule in a Sticky Group, the SLB may 'stick' that connection to the real server specified in the matching rule. 'srcIpSticky' : Stick based on source IP address. 'httpCookieSticky' : Stick based on HTTP Cookie name. 'sslSticky' : Stick based on SSL Session ID. 'undefined' : New sticky type not yet defined. 'destIpSticky' : Stick based on the destination IP address. 'srcDestISticky' : Stick based on the Source and Destionation IP Address. 'httpHeaderSticky' : Stick based on the HTTP Header Name.

SlbMapType.name: SlbMapType
SlbMapType.description: The current type of the Map group. A Map group contains a list of rules matching information in the connection with the HTTP URL, HTTP Cookie, HTTP Header, or HTTP Return Code criteria. 'notCfgMap' : Map type has not been specified. 'urlMap' : HTTP URL matching group. 'cookieMap' : HTTP Cookie matching group. 'headerMap' : HTTP Header field matching group. 'returnCodeMap' : HTTP return code parsing group. 'undefined' : New matching type not yet defined.

SlbReplicationMode.name: SlbReplicationMode
SlbReplicationMode.description: The current replicating option for the virtual server. 'replNone' : Do not replicate any information. 'replAll' : Replicate connection and sticky information. 'replConnection' : Replicate only the connection information. 'replStickyData' : Replicate only the sticky information.

SlbProbeAction.name: SlbProbeAction
SlbProbeAction.description: The current action setting for a probing condition or monitoring condition such as the HTTP return code. 'noAction' : No action. 'logAction' : Logging the event. 'removeAction' : Removing the service. 'countAction' : Counting and logging the event. 'undefined' : New action not yet defined.

SlbVlanType.name: SlbVlanType
SlbVlanType.description: Each configured SLB VLAN has one of the following types : 'clientVlan' : Client side VLAN interface. 'serverVlan' : Server side VLAN interface. 'ftVlan' : Fault Tolerance VLAN interface.

SlbFtState.name: SlbFtState
SlbFtState.description: The current Fault Tolerance state of the SLB entity. 'notConfigFT' : Was not configured with FT. 'initializingFT' : Initializing Fault Tolerance. 'activeFT' : Active FT peer. 'standbyFT' : Standby FT peer.

SlbDirectionalMode.name: SlbDirectionalMode
SlbDirectionalMode.description: The flow direction type of the traffic destined to a particular Virtual Server. 'unidirectional' : traffic only in one direction. 'bidirectional' : traffic in both directions. 'defdirectional' : UDP traffic is unidirection, TCP and other traffics are bidirectional.

cslbxStatsBadSslFormatRejects.name: cslbxStatsBadSslFormatRejects

cslbxStatsL7ParserErrorRejects.name: cslbxStatsL7ParserErrorRejects

cslbxStatsVerMismatchRejects.name: cslbxStatsVerMismatchRejects

cslbxStatsOutOfMemoryRejects.name: cslbxStatsOutOfMemoryRejects

cslbxStatsTimedOutConnections.name: cslbxStatsTimedOutConnections
cslbxStatsTimedOutConnections.description: The number of connections that were terminated because they were idle longer than the configured idle timeout value.

cslbxStatsTcpChecksumErrorPkts.name: cslbxStatsTcpChecksumErrorPkts
cslbxStatsTcpChecksumErrorPkts.description: The accumulated number of TCP packets which have checksum error.

cslbxStatsIpChecksumErrorPkts.name: cslbxStatsIpChecksumErrorPkts
cslbxStatsIpChecksumErrorPkts.description: The accumulated number of IP packets which have checksum error.

cslbxStatsDroppedL4PolicyHCConns.name: cslbxStatsDroppedL4PolicyHCConns
cslbxStatsDroppedL4PolicyHCConns.description: The number of connections dropped by virtual servers with only layer 4 configuration. This object is a 64-bit version of cslbxStatsDroppedL4PolicyConns.

cslbxStatsDroppedL7PolicyHCConns.name: cslbxStatsDroppedL7PolicyHCConns
cslbxStatsDroppedL7PolicyHCConns.description: The number of connections dropped by virtual servers with some layer 7 configuration. This object is a 64-bit version of cslbxStatsDroppedL7PolicyConns.

cslbxStatsNoMatchPolicyHCRejects.name: cslbxStatsNoMatchPolicyHCRejects
cslbxStatsNoMatchPolicyHCRejects.description: The number of connections rejected because they failed to match any configured policy. This object is a 64-bit version of cslbxStatsNoMatchPolicyRejects.

cslbxStatsNoCfgPolicyHCRejects.name: cslbxStatsNoCfgPolicyHCRejects

cslbxStatsAclDenyHCRejects.name: cslbxStatsAclDenyHCRejects
cslbxStatsAclDenyHCRejects.description: The number of connections rejected because the the matching client access list was configured to deny access. This object is a 64-bit version of cslbxStatsAclDenyRejects.

cslbxStatsVerMismatchHCRejects.name: cslbxStatsVerMismatchHCRejects
cslbxStatsVerMismatchHCRejects.description: The number of connections rejected because the Layer 7 configuration was changed while Layer 7 parsing was occurring on the connection. This object is a 64-bit version of cslbxStatsVerMismatchRejects.

cslbxServerFarmTable.name: cslbxServerFarmTable
cslbxServerFarmTable.description: This is a table of server farms, each of which is a group of real servers to be used by SLB for load balancing. It contains additional configurations to the slbSeverFarmTable.

cslbxServerFarmTableEntry.name: cslbxServerFarmTableEntry
cslbxServerFarmTableEntry.description: Additional configuration parameters about a particular server farm served by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxServerFarmHashMaskAddrType.name: cslbxServerFarmHashMaskAddrType
cslbxServerFarmHashMaskAddrType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxServerFarmHashMaskAddr.

cslbxServerFarmHashMaskAddr.name: cslbxServerFarmHashMaskAddr
cslbxServerFarmHashMaskAddr.description: The mask value applied to the IP address before performing IP hashing operation.

cslbxServerFarmClientNatPool.name: cslbxServerFarmClientNatPool
cslbxServerFarmClientNatPool.description: The name of the current client NAT pool associated with this server farm.

cslbxServerFarmFailAction.name: cslbxServerFarmFailAction
cslbxServerFarmFailAction.description: The current action assigned to this server farm when a server has failed ARP or health probe.

cslbxServerFarmHttpReturnCodeMap.name: cslbxServerFarmHttpReturnCodeMap
cslbxServerFarmHttpReturnCodeMap.description: The name of the HTTP return code checking applied to with this server farm.

cslbxServerFarmInFailedThreshold.name: cslbxServerFarmInFailedThreshold
cslbxServerFarmInFailedThreshold.description: The threshold of failed connections before the inband health check taking a server in this farm out-of-service.

cslbxServerFarmInbandResetTimer.name: cslbxServerFarmInbandResetTimer
cslbxServerFarmInbandResetTimer.description: The wait time interval before the inband health check reset a failed server to enable state. The value of zero indicates failed state will never reset.

cslbxServerFarmTransparent.name: cslbxServerFarmTransparent
cslbxServerFarmTransparent.description: This object is used for specifying a transparent server farm. In the transparent mode virtual IP Address to Server IP Address translation does not take place. The value 'true' is used for setting it to transparent mode.

cslbxServerFarmSlowStart.name: cslbxServerFarmSlowStart
cslbxServerFarmSlowStart.reference: slbServerFarmPredictor is a coulmnar object in slbServerFarmTable defined in CISCO-SLB-MIB.
cslbxServerFarmSlowStart.description: This object specifies that the connections to this serverfarm to be in slow start mode. In an environment that uses weighted least connections load balancing, a real server that is placed in service initially has no connections, and could therefore be assigned so many new connections that it becomes overloaded. To prevent such an overload, the slow start feature controls the number of new connections that are directed to a real server that has just been placed in service. This object is applicable if value of slbServerFarmPredictor is 'leastConns'.

cslbxServerFarmHashHeaderName.name: cslbxServerFarmHashHeaderName
cslbxServerFarmHashHeaderName.reference: RFC 2616 Hypertext Transfer Protocol -- HTTP/1.1 Section 5.3.
cslbxServerFarmHashHeaderName.description: This object specifies the HTTP header name. This object is applicable only if the value of slbServerFarmPredictor is 'headerHash'. Following set of Header Name values are supported for this object: Accept Accept-Charset Accept-Encoding Accept-Language Authorization Cache-Control Connection Content-MD5 Expect, From, Host, If-Match Pragma, Referrer, Transfer-Encoding User-Agent, Via.

cslbxServerFarmHashCookieName.name: cslbxServerFarmHashCookieName
cslbxServerFarmHashCookieName.description: This object is used for configuring the HTTP Cookie Name. This object is applicable only if the value of slbSererFarmPredictor is 'cookieHash'.

cslbxServerFarmUrlPatternBegin.name: cslbxServerFarmUrlPatternBegin
cslbxServerFarmUrlPatternBegin.description: The sub-string within the URL string at which to start the hashing operation. The hash result will be used in the server farm with predictor 'urlHash'(slbServerFarmPredictor = 'urlHash'). An empty string indicates hashing should start from the beginning of the URL.

cslbxServerFarmUrlPatternEnd.name: cslbxServerFarmUrlPatternEnd
cslbxServerFarmUrlPatternEnd.description: The sub-string within the URL string at which to end the hashing operation. The hash result will be used in the server farm with predictor 'urlHash'(slbServerFarmPredictor = 'urlHash'). An empty string indicates hashing should stop at the end of the URL.

cslbxServerFarmDescription.name: cslbxServerFarmDescription
cslbxServerFarmDescription.description: This object is used for configuring the description of the server farm.

cslbxServerFarmType.name: cslbxServerFarmType
cslbxServerFarmType.description: This object identifies the type of the serverfarm. The possible values are : redirect(1): Specifies that this server farm is just used for redirecting traffic to new virtual server equivalent. host (2): Specifies typical server farm offering services. This object cannot be changed when the slbServerFarmRowStatus value is 'active'.

cslbxServerFarmState.name: cslbxServerFarmState
cslbxServerFarmState.description: This object identifies the state of the serverfarm. The possible values are : active (1): Specifies that the serverfarm state is active. A serverfarm will be in the active state when atleast one of the realservers configured in this serverfarm is operationaly up and running. inactive(2): Specifies that the serverfarm state is inactive. A serverfarm will be in the inactive state when none of the realservers configured in this serverfarm is operationaly up and running.

cslbxRedirectSvrTable.name: cslbxRedirectSvrTable
cslbxRedirectSvrTable.description: A table of HTTP redirect servers. Entry attributes may be modified regardless of the value of cslbxRedirectSvrState.

cslbxRedirectSvrTableEntry.name: cslbxRedirectSvrTableEntry
cslbxRedirectSvrTableEntry.description: Information about a particular HTTP redirect virtual server in a particular server farm served by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxRedirectSvrName.name: cslbxRedirectSvrName
cslbxRedirectSvrName.description: The name of the Redirect Server

cslbxRedirectSvrRelocationStr.name: cslbxRedirectSvrRelocationStr
cslbxRedirectSvrRelocationStr.description: The relocation URL string sent in the reply of the Redirect Server.

cslbxRedirectSvrBackupString.name: cslbxRedirectSvrBackupString
cslbxRedirectSvrBackupString.description: The backup string sent in the reply of the Redirect Server when the associated real server is disabled.

cslbxRedirectSvrRedirectCode.name: cslbxRedirectSvrRedirectCode
cslbxRedirectSvrRedirectCode.description: The HTTP response code sent in the reply by the Redirect Server.

cslbxRedirectSvrRedirectPort.name: cslbxRedirectSvrRedirectPort
cslbxRedirectSvrRedirectPort.description: The TCP port in the HTTP response sent by the Redirect Server. Instead of the original HTTP port (80), the Redirect Server can tell the client to use a different port (like HTTPS) when connection to the redirected URL destination.

cslbxRedirectSvrState.name: cslbxRedirectSvrState
cslbxRedirectSvrState.description: The current state of the Redirect Server.

cslbxRedirectSvrNumberOfConns.name: cslbxRedirectSvrNumberOfConns
cslbxRedirectSvrNumberOfConns.description: The number TCP and UDP connections currently open on this Redirect Server.

cslbxRedirectSvrMaxConns.name: cslbxRedirectSvrMaxConns
cslbxRedirectSvrMaxConns.description: The maximum number of concurrent open connections the SLB will allow on this Redirect Server.

cslbxRedirectSvrAdminWeight.name: cslbxRedirectSvrAdminWeight
cslbxRedirectSvrAdminWeight.description: The user configured weight of the Redirect Server for the load-balancing algorithms. A weight of zero indicates that no new connections will be assigned to this Redirect Server. Higher weight values indicate to the load-balancing algorithms a higher availability of this Redirect Server to accept more work.

cslbxRedirectSvrOperWeight.name: cslbxRedirectSvrOperWeight
cslbxRedirectSvrOperWeight.description: The actual operating weight of the Redirect Server used by the load-balancing algorithms. This can be adjusted dynamically by DFP. A weight of zero indicates that no new connections will be assigned to this Redirect Server. Higher weight values indicate to the load-balancing algorithms a higher availability of this Redirect Server to accept more work.

cslbxRedirectSvrMetric.name: cslbxRedirectSvrMetric
cslbxRedirectSvrMetric.description: The value used by the least connections load-balancing algorithm. It is the number of connections divided by the actual operating weight. New connections will be given to the server with the smaller metric.

cslbxRedirectSvrTotalConns.name: cslbxRedirectSvrTotalConns
cslbxRedirectSvrTotalConns.description: The total number of connections assigned to this Redirect Server since this server was configured.

cslbxRedirectSvrHCTotalConns.name: cslbxRedirectSvrHCTotalConns
cslbxRedirectSvrHCTotalConns.description: The total number of connections assigned to this Redirect Server since this server was configured. This is the 64-bit version of cslbxRedirectSvrTotalConnections.

cslbxRedirectSvrRowStatus.name: cslbxRedirectSvrRowStatus
cslbxRedirectSvrRowStatus.description: The object used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxRedirectSvrTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxServerFarmProbeTable.name: cslbxServerFarmProbeTable
cslbxServerFarmProbeTable.description: This is a table of probes in the server farms.

cslbxServerFarmProbeTableEntry.name: cslbxServerFarmProbeTableEntry
cslbxServerFarmProbeTableEntry.description: Information about a particular probe associated with a particular server farm, served by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxServerFarmProbeRowStatus.name: cslbxServerFarmProbeRowStatus
cslbxServerFarmProbeRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxServerFarmProbeTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxSfarmHttpReturnCodeTable.name: cslbxSfarmHttpReturnCodeTable
cslbxSfarmHttpReturnCodeTable.description: This table contains the objects that are related to HTTP return code checking in a server farm.

cslbxSfarmHttpReturnCodeEntry.name: cslbxSfarmHttpReturnCodeEntry
cslbxSfarmHttpReturnCodeEntry.description: Information about HTTP return code checking for each server farm. The entry contains information on HTTP Retur Code range, Reset Timer and thresholds for taking actions.

cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeMinValue.name: cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeMinValue
cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeMinValue.reference: RFC 2616 Section 6.1.1 Status Code and Reason Phrase.
cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeMinValue.description: This object is used for configuring the minimum value for HTTP return code checking. When HTTP return code checking is configured, the HTTP responses are monitored for all the balanced HTTP connections. By using return code checking, one can ensure that good content is delivered.

cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeMaxValue.name: cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeMaxValue
cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeMaxValue.reference: RFC 2616 Section 6.1.1 Status Code and Reason Phrase.
cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeMaxValue.description: This object is used for configuring the maximum value for HTTP return error code checking. When HTTP return code checking is configured, the HTTP responses are monitored for all the balanced HTTP connections. By using return code checking, one can ensure that good content is delivered.

cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeActionType.name: cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeActionType
cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeActionType.description: This object defines what actions will be taken if the HTTP return error code checking is done. The value 'countAction' increments the statistics of the number of occurrences of return codes received. The value 'logAction' specifies where syslog messages are sent when a threshold is reached. The value 'removeAction' specifies where the syslog messages are sent when a threshold is reached and the server is removed from the service.

cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeThreshold.name: cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeThreshold
cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeThreshold.description: This object is used for configuring the number of return code occurrences before the action specified in cslbxServerFarmRetCodeActionType is taken. This object is applicable only if the value of cslbxServerFarmRetCodeActionType is 'logAction' or 'removeAction'.

cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeResetTimer.name: cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeResetTimer
cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeResetTimer.description: The wait time interval before the processing can resume. This object is applicable if the value of This object is applicable only if the value of cslbxServerFarmRetCodeActionType is 'logAction' or 'removeAction'.

cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeStorageType.name: cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeStorageType
cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeStorageType.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeRowStatus.name: cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeRowStatus
cslbxSfarmHttpRetCodeRowStatus.description: The object is used for adding/deleting entries in the table. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. This object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1), notInService(2), or notReady(3). All other writable objects may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to notInService(2) or notReady(3).

cslbxServerFarmStatsTable.name: cslbxServerFarmStatsTable
cslbxServerFarmStatsTable.description: This table contains the statistics of server farms

cslbxServerFarmStatsEntry.name: cslbxServerFarmStatsEntry
cslbxServerFarmStatsEntry.description: An entry in cslbxServerFarmStatsTable. Each entry contains statistical information such as current connections, total connections etc.

cslbxServerFarmTotalConns.name: cslbxServerFarmTotalConns
cslbxServerFarmTotalConns.description: The total number of connections loadbalanced to all the real servers associated with this server farm.

cslbxServerFarmCurrConns.name: cslbxServerFarmCurrConns
cslbxServerFarmCurrConns.description: The total number of active connections loadbalanced to all the real servers associated with this server farm.

cslbxServerFarmFailedConns.name: cslbxServerFarmFailedConns
cslbxServerFarmFailedConns.description: The total number of connections failed to all the real servers associated with this server farm. Failure reasons can be Maximum connections reached, Real Server down etc.

cslbxServerFarmNumOfTimeFailOvers.name: cslbxServerFarmNumOfTimeFailOvers
cslbxServerFarmNumOfTimeFailOvers.description: This object contains the value of the number of times a serverfarm has failed over. The failed over state is specified by the cslbxServerFarmState object with a value of inactive(2).

cslbxServerFarmNumOfTimeBkInServs.name: cslbxServerFarmNumOfTimeBkInServs
cslbxServerFarmNumOfTimeBkInServs.description: This object contains the value of the number of times a serverfarm has returned back to inservice after failing over. The inservice state is specified by the cslbxServerFarmState object with a value of active(1).

cslbxNatPoolTable.name: cslbxNatPoolTable
cslbxNatPoolTable.description: A table of IP NAT pools.

cslbxNatPoolEntry.name: cslbxNatPoolEntry
cslbxNatPoolEntry.description: Information about a particular NAT pool served by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxNatPoolName.name: cslbxNatPoolName
cslbxNatPoolName.description: The name of the NAT pool.

cslbxNatPoolStartAddressType.name: cslbxNatPoolStartAddressType
cslbxNatPoolStartAddressType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxNatPoolStartAddress.

cslbxNatPoolStartAddress.name: cslbxNatPoolStartAddress
cslbxNatPoolStartAddress.description: The first IP address in this NAT pool.

cslbxNatPoolEndAddressType.name: cslbxNatPoolEndAddressType
cslbxNatPoolEndAddressType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxNatPoolEndAddress.

cslbxNatPoolEndAddress.name: cslbxNatPoolEndAddress
cslbxNatPoolEndAddress.description: The last IP address in this NAT pool.

cslbxNatPoolRowStatus.name: cslbxNatPoolRowStatus
cslbxNatPoolRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxNatPoolTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxStickyGroupEntry.name: cslbxStickyGroupEntry
cslbxStickyGroupEntry.description: Information about a particular Sticky Group served by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxStickyGroupMaskAddressType.name: cslbxStickyGroupMaskAddressType
cslbxStickyGroupMaskAddressType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxStickyGroupMaskAddress.

cslbxStickyGroupMaskAddress.name: cslbxStickyGroupMaskAddress
cslbxStickyGroupMaskAddress.description: The network mask used with the ipSticky type. The source IP address will be AND'ed with this mask before inserting into the sticky database.

cslbxStickyGroupCookieName.name: cslbxStickyGroupCookieName
cslbxStickyGroupCookieName.description: The HTTP Cookie name used with httpCookieSticky type.

cslbxStickyGroupStickyTimer.name: cslbxStickyGroupStickyTimer
cslbxStickyGroupStickyTimer.description: The length of time a Sticky Group may exist before being automatically removed.

cslbxStickyGroupRowStatus.name: cslbxStickyGroupRowStatus
cslbxStickyGroupRowStatus.description: The row status is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxStickyGroupTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxStickyGroupHeaderName.name: cslbxStickyGroupHeaderName
cslbxStickyGroupHeaderName.description: This object identifies the HTTP Header name. This is applicable only if the value of cslbxStickyGroupType is 'httpHeaderSticky'.

cslbxStickyGroupTimeoutActiveConn.name: cslbxStickyGroupTimeoutActiveConn
cslbxStickyGroupTimeoutActiveConn.description: This object specifies whether the sticky entries to be timed out if active connections exist once the sticky timer expires. If set to 'true', sticky entries will timeout even if connections exist. If set to 'false' sticky entries will not time out if there exist any active connections.

cslbxStickyGroupReplicate.name: cslbxStickyGroupReplicate
cslbxStickyGroupReplicate.description: This object enables/disables sticky replication in a redundant configuration.

cslbxStickyObjectTable.name: cslbxStickyObjectTable
cslbxStickyObjectTable.description: Table of existing sticky entries. Sticky entries allow related connections to be sent to the same real server on a per client basis. This table supports the Content Switching Module (CSM) feature which is not supported by the slbStickyObjectTable in the CISCO-SLB-MIB.

cslbxStickyObjectTableEntry.name: cslbxStickyObjectTableEntry
cslbxStickyObjectTableEntry.description: Information about a particular sticky entry by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxStickyObjectGroupId.name: cslbxStickyObjectGroupId
cslbxStickyObjectGroupId.description: The group ID associated with this sticky entry.

cslbxStickyObjectType.name: cslbxStickyObjectType
cslbxStickyObjectType.description: The sticky type of this sticky entry.

cslbxStickyObjectSourceInfo.name: cslbxStickyObjectSourceInfo
cslbxStickyObjectSourceInfo.description: The client IP address or hashed of source data used created this sticky entry.

cslbxStickyObjectRealAddressType.name: cslbxStickyObjectRealAddressType
cslbxStickyObjectRealAddressType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxStickyObjectRealAddress.

cslbxStickyObjectRealAddress.name: cslbxStickyObjectRealAddress
cslbxStickyObjectRealAddress.description: The real server IP address selected for all clients matched this sticky entry.

cslbxStickyObjectRealPort.name: cslbxStickyObjectRealPort
cslbxStickyObjectRealPort.description: The port number of the real server associated with this sticky entry.

cslbxStickyGroupExtTable.name: cslbxStickyGroupExtTable
cslbxStickyGroupExtTable.description: An extension to cslbxStickyGroupTable. This table contains additional objects related to sticky group.

cslbxStickyGroupExtEntry.name: cslbxStickyGroupExtEntry
cslbxStickyGroupExtEntry.description: An entry in this table. Each entry contains offset, value, secondary cookie etc.

cslbxStickyOffset.name: cslbxStickyOffset
cslbxStickyOffset.description: This object represents the offset value to specify portion of the cookie/header/SSL-ID to use to 'stick' connections. This object is applicable to following values of cslbxStickyGroupType: 'httpCookieSticky' 'sslSticky' 'httpHeaderSticky'.

cslbxStickyLength.name: cslbxStickyLength
cslbxStickyLength.description: This object represents the length of the value specified in cslbxStickyOffset to maintain sticky connections.

cslbxStickyCookieSecondary.name: cslbxStickyCookieSecondary
cslbxStickyCookieSecondary.description: This object is used for configuring the alternate cookie name appearing in URL string to stick a connection.

cslbxStickyCookieInsertEnable.name: cslbxStickyCookieInsertEnable
cslbxStickyCookieInsertEnable.description: This object enables/disables inserting a cookie. The cookie insert feature enables the device to insert a cookie in the 'Set-Cookie' header in the HTTP response.

cslbxStickyCookieExpiryDate.name: cslbxStickyCookieExpiryDate
cslbxStickyCookieExpiryDate.description: This object identifies the valid life time of the cookie. This is the value sent in 'expires=' attribute of 'Set-Cookie' header in the HTTP response.

cslbxMapTable.name: cslbxMapTable
cslbxMapTable.description: Table of SLB map groups. A SLB map group contains a list of matching criteria.

cslbxMapTableEntry.name: cslbxMapTableEntry
cslbxMapTableEntry.description: Information about a particular map group, served by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxMapName.name: cslbxMapName
cslbxMapName.description: The name of the map group.

cslbxMapType.name: cslbxMapType
cslbxMapType.description: The type of the map group.

cslbxMapRowStatus.name: cslbxMapRowStatus
cslbxMapRowStatus.description: The object used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxMapTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxHttpExpressionTable.name: cslbxHttpExpressionTable
cslbxHttpExpressionTable.description: Table of HTTP field and regular expressions.

cslbxHttpExpressionTableEntry.name: cslbxHttpExpressionTableEntry
cslbxHttpExpressionTableEntry.description: Information about a particular HTTP field and the regular expression in a particular map group, served by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxHttpExpressionMapName.name: cslbxHttpExpressionMapName
cslbxHttpExpressionMapName.description: The name of the Map containing this entry. This entry is only valid for cslbxMapType of: 'urlMap', 'cookieMap', or 'headerMap'.

cslbxHttpExpressionIndex.name: cslbxHttpExpressionIndex
cslbxHttpExpressionIndex.description: The index of this item within a Map group.

cslbxHttpExpressionFieldName.name: cslbxHttpExpressionFieldName
cslbxHttpExpressionFieldName.description: The HTTP Cookie Name or Header Name. The SLB device will parse the HTTP packets for this field name. This object is not used for the Map type of 'urlMap', since there is only one HTTP URL field in a HTTP request.

cslbxHttpExpressionValue.name: cslbxHttpExpressionValue
cslbxHttpExpressionValue.description: The regular expression to match against a HTTP URL, Cookie, or Header field.

cslbxHttpExpressionRowStatus.name: cslbxHttpExpressionRowStatus
cslbxHttpExpressionRowStatus.description: The object used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxHttpExpressionTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxHttpExpressionRequestMethod.name: cslbxHttpExpressionRequestMethod
cslbxHttpExpressionRequestMethod.description: The expression string to match against the HTTP request method type string. Some of the standard request methods are: 'GET', 'HEAD', 'POST', 'PUT', 'DELETE', 'TRACE', 'CONNECT', 'OPTIONS'.

cslbxHttpReturnCodeTable.name: cslbxHttpReturnCodeTable
cslbxHttpReturnCodeTable.description: Table of rules associating ReturnCode maps and intervals of HTTP return codes with actions to perform when particular HTTP return codes are seen in the data stream.

cslbxHttpReturnCodeEntry.name: cslbxHttpReturnCodeEntry
cslbxHttpReturnCodeEntry.description: Information about the particular action rule in a particular map of type 'returnCodeMap' dealing with a particular range of HTTP return codes, served by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxHttpReturnCodeMapName.name: cslbxHttpReturnCodeMapName
cslbxHttpReturnCodeMapName.description: The name of the ReturnCode map containing this action rule.

cslbxHttpReturnCodeMinValue.name: cslbxHttpReturnCodeMinValue
cslbxHttpReturnCodeMinValue.reference: RFC 2616 Section 6.1.1 Status Code and Reason Phrase.
cslbxHttpReturnCodeMinValue.description: The minimum HTTP return code that this rule matches.

cslbxHttpReturnCodeMaxValue.name: cslbxHttpReturnCodeMaxValue
cslbxHttpReturnCodeMaxValue.reference: RFC 2616 Section 6.1.1 Status Code and Reason Phrase.
cslbxHttpReturnCodeMaxValue.description: The maximum HTTP return code that this rule matches.

cslbxHttpReturnCodeThreshold.name: cslbxHttpReturnCodeThreshold
cslbxHttpReturnCodeThreshold.description: The number of times the return code seen before the action taking place. Once HTTP return codes between cslbxHttpReturnCodeMinValue and cslbxHttpReturnCodeMaxValue, inclusive, have been seen at least cslbxHttpReturnCodeThreshold times, the action specified by cslbxHttpReturnCodeType is taken. The value of zero indicates this object has not been set.

cslbxHttpReturnCodeResetTimer.name: cslbxHttpReturnCodeResetTimer
cslbxHttpReturnCodeResetTimer.description: The time interval before resetting the state of the real server. Once the action associated with this rule is taken, the associated real server state is reset after cslbxHttpReturnCodeResetTimer. The value of zero indicates the state will never reset.

cslbxHttpReturnCodeType.name: cslbxHttpReturnCodeType
cslbxHttpReturnCodeType.description: The action associated with this rule.

cslbxHttpReturnCodeRowStatus.name: cslbxHttpReturnCodeRowStatus
cslbxHttpReturnCodeRowStatus.description: The object used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxHttpReturnCodeTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxPolicyTableEntry.name: cslbxPolicyTableEntry
cslbxPolicyTableEntry.description: Information about a particular policy configured on a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxPolicyClientGroupNumber.name: cslbxPolicyClientGroupNumber
cslbxPolicyClientGroupNumber.description: The group number of the associated client access list.

cslbxPolicyClientGroupName.name: cslbxPolicyClientGroupName
cslbxPolicyClientGroupName.description: The group name of the associated client access list.

cslbxPolicyUrlMap.name: cslbxPolicyUrlMap
cslbxPolicyUrlMap.description: The name of the associated URL map.

cslbxPolicyCookieMap.name: cslbxPolicyCookieMap
cslbxPolicyCookieMap.description: The name of the associated Cookie map.

cslbxPolicyGenericHeaderMap.name: cslbxPolicyGenericHeaderMap
cslbxPolicyGenericHeaderMap.description: The name of the associated generic HTTP header map.

cslbxPolicyStickyGroup.name: cslbxPolicyStickyGroup
cslbxPolicyStickyGroup.description: The number of the associated sticky group. The value '0' indicates no sticky group is associated.

cslbxPolicyDscpEnabled.name: cslbxPolicyDscpEnabled
cslbxPolicyDscpEnabled.description: The current setting for enabling TOS byte stamping. If this is set, the TCP TOS (type-of-service) byte of traffic matching this policy will be stamped with the cslbxPolicyDscpStamping value.

cslbxPolicyDscpStamping.name: cslbxPolicyDscpStamping
cslbxPolicyDscpStamping.description: The value to be stamped over the TCP TOS (type-of-service) byte.

cslbxPolicyFarmName.name: cslbxPolicyFarmName
cslbxPolicyFarmName.description: The server farm to which a connection matching this policy may be assigned.

cslbxPolicyRowStatus.name: cslbxPolicyRowStatus
cslbxPolicyRowStatus.description: The object used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxPolicyTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxPolicyBackupFarmName.name: cslbxPolicyBackupFarmName
cslbxPolicyBackupFarmName.description: The backup server farm to be used in case the primary server farm has no active server.

cslbxPolicyBkFarmStickyEnabled.name: cslbxPolicyBkFarmStickyEnabled
cslbxPolicyBkFarmStickyEnabled.description: The current setting for enabling sticky option on the backup server farm.

cslbxPolicyReverseStickyGroup.name: cslbxPolicyReverseStickyGroup
cslbxPolicyReverseStickyGroup.description: The group number of the sticky group to be used when inserting reverse sticky entry. The value of zero indicates that reverse sticky is not enabled.

cslbxVirtualServerTable.name: cslbxVirtualServerTable
cslbxVirtualServerTable.description: Table of virtual servers. It contains additional configurations for the slbVirtualServerTable.

cslbxVirtualServerTableEntry.name: cslbxVirtualServerTableEntry
cslbxVirtualServerTableEntry.description: Additional configuration information about a particular virtual server served by a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxVirtualAdvertiseOption.name: cslbxVirtualAdvertiseOption
cslbxVirtualAdvertiseOption.description: The advertise option for the virtual IP address. This value and the cslbxVirtualAdvertise value will determine whether and when to add the virtual IP address into the static route table.

cslbxVirtualVlanId.name: cslbxVirtualVlanId
cslbxVirtualVlanId.description: The VLAN ID associated with the virtual server. Only traffic from this VLAN may match the virtual server. By default (value of zero), a virtual server may match traffic from any VLAN.

cslbxVirtualReplicationMode.name: cslbxVirtualReplicationMode
cslbxVirtualReplicationMode.description: Specifies which information will be replicated from the active device to a standby device in a fault tolerant configuration.

cslbxVirtualPendingTimer.name: cslbxVirtualPendingTimer
cslbxVirtualPendingTimer.description: The length of time before a connection in the pending state gets torn down.

cslbxVirtualL7MaxParseLength.name: cslbxVirtualL7MaxParseLength
cslbxVirtualL7MaxParseLength.description: The maximum number of characters to be parsed for Layer 7 (application level) specific information. If HTTP processing is required on an HTTP request or response with HTTP header length greater than cslbxVirtualL7MaxParseLength, the connection will be rejected and reset.

cslbxVirtualHttpPersistenceSlb.name: cslbxVirtualHttpPersistenceSlb
cslbxVirtualHttpPersistenceSlb.description: The setting for load balancing each request in a HTTP 1.1 persistence connection. If set to 'true', the SLB device may direct successive HTTP requests in the same TCP connection to different destinations.

cslbxVirtualURLHashBeginString.name: cslbxVirtualURLHashBeginString
cslbxVirtualURLHashBeginString.description: The sub-string within the URL string at which to start the hashing operation. The hash result will be used in the server farm with predictor 'urlHash'. An empty string indicates hashing should begin at the beginning of the URL.

cslbxVirtualURLHashEndString.name: cslbxVirtualURLHashEndString
cslbxVirtualURLHashEndString.description: The sub-string within the URL string at which to end the hashing operation. The hash result will be used in the server farm with predictor 'urlHash'. An empty string indicates hashing should end at the end of the URL.

cslbxVirtualMaxConns.name: cslbxVirtualMaxConns
cslbxVirtualMaxConns.description: The maximum number of connections can be concurrently opened to this virtual server. The value of zero indicates that there is no upper limit of connections to this virtual server.

cslbxVirtualOwnerName.name: cslbxVirtualOwnerName
cslbxVirtualOwnerName.description: The name of the associated Owner.

cslbxVirtualFlowMode.name: cslbxVirtualFlowMode
cslbxVirtualFlowMode.description: The direction of the traffic flowing through the SLB device.

cslbxVirtualSSLStickyOffset.name: cslbxVirtualSSLStickyOffset
cslbxVirtualSSLStickyOffset.description: The number of bytes offset into the SSL session ID where the sticky data started.

cslbxVirtualSSLStickyLength.name: cslbxVirtualSSLStickyLength
cslbxVirtualSSLStickyLength.description: The number of bytes of SSL session ID to be used as sticky data.

cslbxVirtualReverseStickyGroup.name: cslbxVirtualReverseStickyGroup
cslbxVirtualReverseStickyGroup.description: The group number of the sticky group to be used when inserting reverse sticky entry. The value of zero indicates that reverse sticky is not enabled.

cslbxVirtualBackupFarmName.name: cslbxVirtualBackupFarmName
cslbxVirtualBackupFarmName.description: The backup server farm to be used in case the primary server farm has no active server.

cslbxVirtualBkFarmStickyEnabled.name: cslbxVirtualBkFarmStickyEnabled
cslbxVirtualBkFarmStickyEnabled.description: The current setting for enabling sticky option on the backup server farm.

cslbxRuleTable.name: cslbxRuleTable
cslbxRuleTable.description: This table provides the function to apply the policies to the virtual servers. Using different policies, the SLB can direct traffic matching different patterns to different server farms.

cslbxRuleEntry.name: cslbxRuleEntry
cslbxRuleEntry.description: This entry links one SLB policy to a virtual server. If the status of associated cslbxRuleVirtualServerName or the status of associated cslbxRulePolicyName is not active, the status of this entry cannot be active.

cslbxRuleVirtualServerName.name: cslbxRuleVirtualServerName
cslbxRuleVirtualServerName.description: The name of the associated virtual server.

cslbxRulePolicyName.name: cslbxRulePolicyName
cslbxRulePolicyName.description: The name of the associated SLB policy.

cslbxRuleCurrentConnections.name: cslbxRuleCurrentConnections
cslbxRuleCurrentConnections.description: The current number of open connections that matched this SLB policy.

cslbxRuleTotalConnections.name: cslbxRuleTotalConnections
cslbxRuleTotalConnections.description: The total number of connections that ever matched this SLB policy.

cslbxRuleHCTotalConnections.name: cslbxRuleHCTotalConnections
cslbxRuleHCTotalConnections.description: The total number of connections that ever matched this SLB policy. This is the 64-bit version of cslbxRuleTotalConnections.

cslbxRuleTotalClientPackets.name: cslbxRuleTotalClientPackets
cslbxRuleTotalClientPackets.description: The total number of packets ever sent by the client to the server on a connection that matched this SLB policy.

cslbxRuleHCTotalClientPackets.name: cslbxRuleHCTotalClientPackets
cslbxRuleHCTotalClientPackets.description: The total number of packets ever sent by the client to the server on a connection that matched this SLB policy. This is the 64-bit version of cslbxRuleTotalClientPackets.

cslbxRuleTotalServerPackets.name: cslbxRuleTotalServerPackets
cslbxRuleTotalServerPackets.description: The total number of packets ever sent by the server to the client on a connection that matched this SLB policy.

cslbxRuleHCTotalServerPackets.name: cslbxRuleHCTotalServerPackets
cslbxRuleHCTotalServerPackets.description: The total number of packets ever sent by the server to the client on a connection that matched this SLB policy. This is the 64-bit version of cslbxRuleTotalServerPackets.

cslbxRuleRowStatus.name: cslbxRuleRowStatus
cslbxRuleRowStatus.description: The object used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxRuleTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxRuleTotalClientOctets.name: cslbxRuleTotalClientOctets
cslbxRuleTotalClientOctets.description: The total number of octets ever sent by the client to the server on a connection that matched this SLB policy.

cslbxRuleHCTotalClientOctets.name: cslbxRuleHCTotalClientOctets
cslbxRuleHCTotalClientOctets.description: The total number of octets ever sent by the client to the server on a connection that matched this SLB policy. This is the 64-bit version of cslbxRuleTotalClientOctets.

cslbxRuleTotalServerOctets.name: cslbxRuleTotalServerOctets
cslbxRuleTotalServerOctets.description: The total number of octets ever sent by the server to the client on a connection that matched this SLB policy.

cslbxRuleHCTotalServerOctets.name: cslbxRuleHCTotalServerOctets
cslbxRuleHCTotalServerOctets.description: The total number of octets ever sent by the server to the client on a connection that matched this SLB policy. This is the 64-bit version of cslbxRuleTotalServerOctets.

cslbxVlanTable.name: cslbxVlanTable
cslbxVlanTable.description: This table provides the configuration of VLANs configured on the SLB.

cslbxVlanEntry.name: cslbxVlanEntry
cslbxVlanEntry.description: This entry is for configuring the VLAN on the SLB device.

cslbxVlanId.name: cslbxVlanId
cslbxVlanId.description: The 802.1q VLAN ID of this VLAN.

cslbxVlanAddressType.name: cslbxVlanAddressType
cslbxVlanAddressType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxVlanAddress.

cslbxVlanAddress.name: cslbxVlanAddress
cslbxVlanAddress.description: The IP address of this VLAN interface.

cslbxVlanMaskAddressType.name: cslbxVlanMaskAddressType
cslbxVlanMaskAddressType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxVlanMaskAddress.

cslbxVlanMaskAddress.name: cslbxVlanMaskAddress
cslbxVlanMaskAddress.description: The network mask for this VLAN interface.

cslbxVlanRowStatus.name: cslbxVlanRowStatus
cslbxVlanRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxVlanTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxAliasAddrTable.name: cslbxAliasAddrTable
cslbxAliasAddrTable.description: This table provides the configuration of alias IP addresses on the SLB device. The SLB device will respond to an ARP request for alias IP addresses if the ARP request arrives on the configured VLAN. A given VLAN may be associated with multiple alias IP addresses.

cslbxAliasAddrEntry.name: cslbxAliasAddrEntry
cslbxAliasAddrEntry.description: This entry is for configuring an alias IP address on the SLB device.

cslbxAliasAddrVlanId.name: cslbxAliasAddrVlanId
cslbxAliasAddrVlanId.description: The VLAN ID associated with this alias address.

cslbxAliasAddrAddressType.name: cslbxAliasAddrAddressType
cslbxAliasAddrAddressType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxAliasAddrAddress.

cslbxAliasAddrRowStatus.name: cslbxAliasAddrRowStatus
cslbxAliasAddrRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxAliasAddrTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxStaticRouteTable.name: cslbxStaticRouteTable
cslbxStaticRouteTable.description: This table provides the configuration of static routes on the SLB device.

cslbxStaticRouteEntry.name: cslbxStaticRouteEntry
cslbxStaticRouteEntry.description: This entry is for configuring the static route used by the SLB device. The SLB device will accept multiple destination gateways for the same route. The SLB should able to pick an active gateway for a given route. In some case, the SLB device can load-balancing among the gateways of the same route.

cslbxStaticRouteVlanId.name: cslbxStaticRouteVlanId
cslbxStaticRouteVlanId.description: The VLAN ID associated with this route.

cslbxStaticRouteSubnetAddrType.name: cslbxStaticRouteSubnetAddrType
cslbxStaticRouteSubnetAddrType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxStaticRouteSubnetAddr.

cslbxStaticRouteSubnetAddr.name: cslbxStaticRouteSubnetAddr
cslbxStaticRouteSubnetAddr.description: The IP subnet of this route.

cslbxStaticRouteMaskAddrType.name: cslbxStaticRouteMaskAddrType
cslbxStaticRouteMaskAddrType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxStaticRouteMaskAddr.

cslbxStaticRouteMaskAddr.name: cslbxStaticRouteMaskAddr
cslbxStaticRouteMaskAddr.description: The IP network mask of this route.

cslbxStaticRouteGatewayAddrType.name: cslbxStaticRouteGatewayAddrType
cslbxStaticRouteGatewayAddrType.description: The type of address stored in cslbxStaticRouteGatewayAddr.

cslbxStaticRouteGatewayAddr.name: cslbxStaticRouteGatewayAddr
cslbxStaticRouteGatewayAddr.description: The IP address of the next hop gateway.

cslbxStaticRouteRowStatus.name: cslbxStaticRouteRowStatus
cslbxStaticRouteRowStatus.description: The object is used by a management station to create or delete the row entry in cslbxStaticRouteTable following the RowStatus textual convention.

cslbxFtTableEntry.name: cslbxFtTableEntry
cslbxFtTableEntry.description: Information about Fault Tolerance settings for a particular local SLB entity.

cslbxFtVlanId.name: cslbxFtVlanId
cslbxFtVlanId.description: The VLAN ID used by this Fault Tolerance group.

cslbxFtPreempt.name: cslbxFtPreempt
cslbxFtPreempt.description: The preemption setting for this Fault Tolerance group.

cslbxFtPriority.name: cslbxFtPriority
cslbxFtPriority.description: The priority value of this SLB device for the Fault Tolerance group.

cslbxFtHeartBeatTimer.name: cslbxFtHeartBeatTimer
cslbxFtHeartBeatTimer.description: The time interval of sending the keep-alive messages to the peer in the Fault Tolerance group.

cslbxFtFailThreshold.name: cslbxFtFailThreshold
cslbxFtFailThreshold.description: The threshold for failing over to the standby SLB. If a standby SLB device has not received a keep-alive message from an active SLB device within cslbxFtFailThreshold consecutive periods of length cslbxFtHeartBeatTimer, the standby will become active.

cslbxFtState.name: cslbxFtState
cslbxFtState.description: The current Fault Tolerance state of this SLB device.

cslbxFtStateChangeTime.name: cslbxFtStateChangeTime
cslbxFtStateChangeTime.description: The time of the last change in the current Fault Tolerance state of the SLB device.
